flawed_nl_solution:
If there are 92 students and 20 students take the bus home, the number of students who haven't taken the bus is 92-20 = <<92-20=27>>27 students.
5/8 of the students who didn't take the bus home ride bikes home, a total of 5/8* 27 = <<5/8*27=135/8>>135/8 students.
The number of students who neither took the bus nor biked home but walked home is 27-135/8 = <<27-135/8=81/8>>81/8
#### 81/8
